title: KSL Pickem: College football week 5 staff selections
text:
 
SALT LAKE CITY — How did you do in week 4? If you're like most of us, you didn't see East Carolina beating Virginia Tech or Utah dismantling the Oregon Ducks. Consensus picks were 2-3 for the week, down from 4-1 in each of the first three weeks of the season. 
The good news is that the slate has been wiped clean and we have a new opportunity to play KSL College Football Pick'em. 
BYU and Utah State return home, with the Cougars facing Connecticut tonight and the Aggies hosting Colorado State on Saturday. 
Other matchups for KSL Pick'em in Week 5: No. 19 Wisconsin vs. Iowa; Navy vs. Air Force; and No. 20 Oklahoma State vs. Kansas State. 
Utah has the week off. 
To play KSL College Football Pick'em, click HERE or download the KSL GameCenter app on iOS or Android devices. 
One big change you will notice this week is that auto-save has been turned off. After inserting the predicted score for each game, hit the "Save Pick" button to submit. If successful, the box will change from red to green. 
If you haven't signed up yet, don't worry — each weekly prize ($30 Wells Fargo VISA gift card) will be awarded to the highest point total for that week, so you have the same odds to win as those who participated in weeks 1-4.
